if \[\lim_{n\to\infty} a_n = a\,.\]
  

A sequence is $\lbrace a\rbrace_n$ is said to be Cauchy, if
$\forall~\varepsilon > 0~ \exists~ N\in\mathbb{N}$
such that if $n>N$ and $m>N$ then $|a_n - a_m| < \varepsilon$.

