    \[\int x^n~dx = \frac{1}{n+1}x^{n+1}\]
    So by linearity,
    \begin{align}
      \int \sum_{k=0}^{n}a_k x^n~dx &= \sum_{k=0}^{n} \int a_k x^n~dx\\
      & = \sum_{k=0}^{n} a_k \int x^n~dx\\
